TITLE: Secure Database Connection in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a SecureDatabase class that establishes a secure connection using an encrypted configuration string, which is essential for protecting sensitive database credentials.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/blob/main/docs/notes/secrets-management.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class SecureDatabase {
    private connection: Connection;

    constructor(encryptedConfig: string) {
        const config = this.decryptConfig(encryptedConfig);
        this.connection = new Connection(config);
    }

    private decryptConfig(encrypted: string): DatabaseConfig {
        // Implement decryption logic
        return JSON.parse(decrypted);
    }
}
```

