TITLE: Managing Processing Queues in Eliza
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to implement a QueueManager for processing sequential tasks in Eliza. The manager handles queue state to prevent concurrent processing and processes items until the queue is empty.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/blob/main/docs/notes/advanced.md#2025-04-16_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class QueueManager {
    private queue: string[] = [];
    private processing: boolean = false;

    async processQueue(): Promise<void> {
        if (this.processing || this.queue.length === 0) {
            return;
        }

        this.processing = true;
        while (this.queue.length > 0) {
            const item = this.queue.shift();
            await this.processItem(item);
        }
        this.processing = false;
    }
}
```

