TITLE: Resource Cleanup and Reconnection in TypeScript Client Manager
DESCRIPTION: Implements resource cleanup and reconnection methods in a client manager class. The cleanup method handles closing connections, clearing caches, and canceling timers, while the reconnect method orchestrates a complete connection reset.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/blob/main/docs/notes/clients.md#2025-04-16_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class ClientManager {
    private async cleanup() {
        // Close connections
        await Promise.all(this.connections.map((conn) => conn.close()));

        // Clear caches
        this.cache.clear();

        // Cancel timers
        this.timers.forEach((timer) => clearInterval(timer));
    }

    private async reconnect() {
        await this.cleanup();
        await wait(this.calculateBackoff());
        await this.initialize();
    }
}
```

