TITLE: Formatting Git Log to JSON with Bash
DESCRIPTION: This Bash command formats the Git log of the past month into a JSON array containing fields like commit, author, date, and message. It utilizes the Git log command with specific formatting and sed for proper JSON array formatting. This command requires Git and sed to be installed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/blob/main/docs/community/Notes/cookbook.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
git log --since=\"1 month ago\" --date=short --pretty=format:'{"commit": "%H", "author": "%an", "date": "%ad", "message": "%s"}' | sed '1s/^/[\n/; $!s/$/,/; $s/$/\n]/' > 1month.json
```

