TITLE: Retrieving TEE Logs using cURL with Query Parameters (Bash)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use cURL to send a POST request to retrieve TEE logs. It includes optional query parameters for filtering logs based on various criteria such as agentId, roomId, userId, and more.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/blob/main/packages/client-direct/src/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
curl -X POST --location "http://localhost:3000/tee/logs" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{
          "query": {
            "agentId": "75490f32-c06a-0005-9804-339453d3fe2f"
          },
          "page": 1,
          "pageSize": 10
        }'
```

